summary:
Jon has always had an unfavourable opinion over how people treated him over his bastard status, and rightly so. 
For shippers...
body:
Political Jon and why it makes him Out Of Character

Jon has always had an unfavourable opinion over how people treated him over his bastard status, and rightly so.

For shippers who like to parallel Sansa posing as Alayne in A Feast For Crows and Jon being born a bastard, none really understand what it actually MEANS for him. Not only this, but the Ned and Cat 2.0 parallels also don’t match, because why would Jon want to marry a woman similar to the one who emotionally neglected and abused him? To the point of wishing for his death twice? It’s LITTLEFINGER who’s obsessed with the Catelyn parallels, not Jon. He doesn’t view Sansa as another Catelyn.

Sure, it was how society at the time worked and the Starks did accommodate Jon better than other noble families would their bastards, but there were still clear effects on Jon’s self esteem and self perception over his status in feudal Westeros. He still felt the negative ramifications of it deeply and angrily. Sansa herself, in the television series admits to treating him awfully when she was a child, mirroring how her mother and other members of nobility viewed him.

So why would Jon prove every assumption people negatively had of him? That he was a scheming and manipulative bastard willing to backstab someone? Sure, in the political!Jon theory it’s to protect the Northerners, but it’s against his character for this reason. He was shunned simply for something he HAD NOT DONE YET, Catelyn was paranoid he would plot his way to become Lord of Winterfell, over the trueborn heir she had given birth to, Robb. Jon is a total condradiction of her belief on bastards. He loves his siblings, he protects his home and retakes it from another bastard claiming Lordship over Winterfell. Ramsay was his narrative foil. Why is it a good thing for them to perceive Jon as a possessive and easily jealous man?

Jon is constantly described as being honest and trusting, to the point where he himself was betrayed and killed by men he believed were loyal to him, while Commander of the Wall. So not only does how his experience growing up affect him, but Jon is clearly disgusted by the concept of betrayal as a whole. His family were backstabbed. So was he. He DIED himself because of it, along with his father and brother and had traitors HANGED. The Starks VALUE loyalty to the point other noble houses see it as something they can take advantage of and have, many times.

Why would he do the same to Daenerys after everything he’s been through?

I don’t support Jonerys myself, but it’s ridiculous for certain Jonsa stans to simply jump through hoops and make all these baseless theories trying to come across as ‘superior intellectuals compared to the dumb general audience who don’t get subtext and literary analysis’. They just come across as complete and utter assholes. Just like any other shipping group that slate off the GA as dumb and harp on about ‘subtext’. It’s a tv show.

summary:
Jon x Sansa: Riverdale AU
When Sansa convinced Jon to help her investigate the mysterious disappearance of Jeyne Poole, she...
body:
Jon x Sansa: Riverdale AU

When Sansa convinced Jon to help her investigate the mysterious disappearance of Jeyne Poole, she hadn’t expected it to lead them down a twisted path of conspiracies and cover-ups older than she was. Who was this shadowy “Spider” and what did he know of Jon’s parentage? Where are all the young girls vanishing to? And what does a “Mockingjay” have to do with it? When the truth comes out and the dust settles, the only thing Sansa can be sure of is her and Jon… because well, they’re endgame.

for @stark for @jonsasecretsanta2018

summary: The Starks will be unstoppable in season 8.
title: The Starks will be unstoppable in season 8.
body:
The show started out rough for the Stark’s but season 8 will be their season. We have the magical three-eyed raven, a skilled master assassin, a potential young queen who is kind and fast becoming a master of the Game and Jon Snow a skilled warrior who just so happens to be the heir to the Iron Throne. They have the allegiance of the North and Vale and loyal support from from the likes of Sam, Brienne and soon Jaime. It’s true that anything could happen, but House of Stark has been through a lot and are likely to come out stronger than ever this final season.

I am sooo excited you guys and can not wait !!!!
